WEBVTT

00:00.674 --> 00:02.110
- [buzzing]
- [distant singing]

00:02.153 --> 00:04.329
The Green family
singing karaoke?

00:04.373 --> 00:06.331
This will certainly be
a delight.

00:06.375 --> 00:08.290
I can't wait to sing,
and by sing, I mean,

00:08.333 --> 00:10.466
make fart noises into the mic.
Like so...

00:10.510 --> 00:12.076
- [deep inhale]
- No, Cricket.

00:12.120 --> 00:14.557
Remy, I'm a little surprised
you wanted to join us.

00:14.601 --> 00:16.167
- Do you like singing?
- Uh-huh!

00:16.211 --> 00:18.561
I sometimes sneak out of
choir lessons and come here

00:18.605 --> 00:20.650
to practice my
ecclesiastical songs, instead.

00:20.694 --> 00:21.999
Naughty, Remy.

00:22.043 --> 00:23.871
Wow, I can't wait sing.

00:23.914 --> 00:26.264
Yeah!
I'm itchin' for that limelight!

00:26.308 --> 00:27.875
Well, Ma,
we gotta wait our turn.

00:27.918 --> 00:29.920
I got the programmer!

00:29.964 --> 00:32.619
I had to fight someone! Had to
pull out the ol' chompers.

00:32.662 --> 00:34.969
[chomps]
So, who's ready to pick a song?

00:35.012 --> 00:36.971
Whoa! Hold on there,
little guru.

00:37.014 --> 00:39.887
Picking a karaoke song
is no careless task.

00:39.930 --> 00:41.279
Uh, who are you?

00:41.323 --> 00:43.325
Why, I'm Kara Karaoke.

00:43.368 --> 00:45.936
And I own this
little slice of Shangri-la.

00:45.980 --> 00:48.852
Karaoke is one of the purest
forms of self-expression.

00:48.896 --> 00:51.681
It fosters a sense of
community and belonging.

00:51.725 --> 00:53.857
So, dear family, choose wisely

00:53.901 --> 00:56.860
[singing]
and find where you belong!

00:56.904 --> 00:59.602
Find where I belong?
Oh, my, my, my, my...

00:59.646 --> 01:02.170
Uh-oh. I'm hearing some
my-mying?

01:02.213 --> 01:03.519
- ...my, my...
- [Nancy] Till?

01:03.563 --> 01:04.999
Sorry, Mama, I'm just feeling

01:05.042 --> 01:08.002
an awful lot of pressure
to find my perfect song.

01:08.045 --> 01:09.699
There are just <i>so many</i> options.

01:09.743 --> 01:13.137
Do I belong in pop?
Hip hop? Medieval folk rock?

01:13.181 --> 01:15.357
What if there's nothing
that represents me?

01:15.400 --> 01:18.012
[gasps] This is
quite the ordeal for Tilly!

01:18.055 --> 01:19.970
Picking a song should be fun.

01:20.014 --> 01:22.233
[gasps] I know!
We'll help you find one.

01:22.277 --> 01:24.584
Here, I'll go first
to show you how I'd do it.

01:24.627 --> 01:26.542
Oh! This one's
one of my favorites!

01:26.586 --> 01:28.849
It reminds me of an old flame.

01:28.892 --> 01:30.981
Which one is he... Oh, Bill.

01:31.025 --> 01:32.940
-Hello, I'm Bill Green,
-[feedback]

01:32.983 --> 01:35.943
and I'm going to sing a song.

01:35.986 --> 01:38.815
<i>♪ I will always remember when</i>

01:38.859 --> 01:41.383
<i>♪ You and I'd meet up again</i>

01:41.426 --> 01:44.299
<i>♪ A flash of red
Ready for adventure ♪</i>

01:44.342 --> 01:48.303
<i>♪ I love the times
When we're together ♪</i>

01:48.346 --> 01:51.088
<i>♪ 'Cause there's one thing
A man can never give up ♪</i>

01:51.132 --> 01:54.091
<i>♪ And that's the burnin' love
for his red pickup ♪</i>

01:54.135 --> 01:55.919
[Nancy]
Oh, Bill!

01:55.963 --> 01:58.313
<i>♪ You'll always be
My number one ♪</i>

01:58.356 --> 02:01.403
<i>♪ When we're together
We have fun ♪</i>

02:01.446 --> 02:04.188
<i>♪ Through the rain, the dirt,
The snow, the muck ♪</i>

02:04.232 --> 02:08.932
<i>♪ I can never give up
My pick-up truck ♪</i>

02:08.976 --> 02:11.674
<i>♪ Carried lumber
With no complainin' ♪</i>

02:11.718 --> 02:14.416
<i>♪ V-8 engine
Never strainin' ♪</i>

02:14.459 --> 02:16.984
<i>♪ If I was to somehow
Up and quit you ♪</i>

02:17.027 --> 02:20.074
<i>♪ I guarantee
I won't forget you ♪</i>

02:20.117 --> 02:22.946
<i>♪ You'll always be
My number one ♪</i>

02:22.990 --> 02:25.688
<i>♪ When we're together
We have fun ♪</i>

02:25.732 --> 02:28.648
<i>♪ Through the rain, the dirt,
The snow, the muck ♪</i>

02:28.691 --> 02:33.174
<i>♪ I can never give up
My pickup truck. ♪</i>

02:33.217 --> 02:35.089
- [applause]
- Thank you, everybody!

02:35.132 --> 02:37.004
Very passionate, Mr. Green!

02:37.047 --> 02:39.789
Yeah, you usually break
into tears during the bridge.

02:39.833 --> 02:41.704
Aw, thanks guys.
But how about you, Tilly?

02:41.748 --> 02:43.793
Think you might wanna
try a song like that?

02:43.837 --> 02:46.491
Papa, your song
was a perfect fit for you,

02:46.535 --> 02:48.885
but I'm not sure
it's a song for Tilly.

02:48.929 --> 02:51.453
Well, when I'm having trouble
figuring stuff out

02:51.496 --> 02:53.498
or I'm feeling
all pent up inside,

02:53.542 --> 02:56.501
I like to do something
with a little attitude.

02:56.545 --> 02:58.808
[hard rock music playing]

02:58.852 --> 03:00.810
<i>Huh!</i>

03:00.854 --> 03:05.467
<i>♪ Oh, authority is not for me
This I know is true! ♪</i>

03:05.510 --> 03:07.687
<i>♪ I'll push a door
That says to pull ♪</i>

03:07.730 --> 03:09.689
<i>♪ Don't tell me what to do!</i>

03:09.732 --> 03:11.952
<i>- ♪ So, back off! Back up!
- ♪ Back off! Back up!</i>

03:11.995 --> 03:13.954
<i>♪ Time to move
And pack it up ♪</i>

03:13.997 --> 03:16.347
<i>- ♪ Check in! Check out!
- ♪ Check in! Check out!</i>

03:16.391 --> 03:18.523
<i>♪ Raise your voice
It's time to shout! ♪</i>

03:18.567 --> 03:20.134
[screams]

03:20.177 --> 03:22.571
<i>♪ So don't listen
To your teachers ♪</i>

03:22.614 --> 03:24.616
<i>♪ Or the TV weatherman</i>

03:24.660 --> 03:26.880
<i>♪ Your response to everyone</i>

03:26.923 --> 03:28.838
<i>♪ Is to kick them in the can!</i>

03:28.882 --> 03:31.362
<i>- ♪ So, back off! Back up!
- ♪ Back off! Back up!</i>

03:31.406 --> 03:33.364
<i>♪ Time to move
And pack it up ♪</i>

03:33.408 --> 03:35.758
<i>- ♪ Check in! Check out!
- ♪ Check in! Check out!</i>

03:35.802 --> 03:37.586
<i>♪ Tell 'em what
You're all about! ♪</i>

03:37.629 --> 03:39.501
♪ <i>Back off!</i> ♪

03:39.544 --> 03:42.939
[continues note]

03:42.983 --> 03:44.680
[panting]

03:44.724 --> 03:45.986
[sweetly]
Thanks, everyone!

03:46.029 --> 03:47.770
Hope you had
as much fun as I did!

03:47.814 --> 03:49.467
- Whoa.
- Hey, y'all!

03:49.511 --> 03:50.860
So, what did you think?

03:50.904 --> 03:52.253
That song just makes me wanna

03:52.296 --> 03:53.907
shove people around
and break stuff!

03:53.950 --> 03:56.083
Son, she doesn't
actually want you to go out

03:56.126 --> 03:58.389
and destroy things.
She was using metaphors.

03:58.433 --> 04:00.261
Well, I thought
your explosive lyrics

04:00.304 --> 04:02.611
were both thrilling
and profound, Mama.

04:02.654 --> 04:04.787
But I can't help wonder
if my one true song

04:04.831 --> 04:06.180
is still out there.

04:06.223 --> 04:07.834
Well, you'll never find it

04:07.877 --> 04:10.401
if you keep listening to
their awful music!

04:10.445 --> 04:11.838
Oh, boy, here we go.

04:11.881 --> 04:13.883
Everything new
sounds exactly the same!

04:13.927 --> 04:15.232
Like garbage!

04:15.276 --> 04:17.626
What happened to
the good ol' classics

04:17.669 --> 04:19.062
everyone used to sing?

04:19.106 --> 04:21.978
Like "Choo-choo Gotchu,"
or "Honeybee Mondays"?

04:22.022 --> 04:25.329
- Are those real songs, Gramma?
- I don't know what that is.

04:25.373 --> 04:27.810
I'll prove to y'all
they're classics for a reason!

04:27.854 --> 04:31.683
Don't you worry, Tilly!
Gramma knows the song for you.

04:31.727 --> 04:35.383
['30s music playing]

04:35.426 --> 04:39.343
<i>♪ When you're in a bind
And not sure what to do ♪</i>

04:39.387 --> 04:43.173
<i>♪ You might be tempted
To try something new ♪</i>

04:43.217 --> 04:46.960
<i>♪ But no, don't do it!
Stick with the classics ♪</i>

04:47.003 --> 04:50.398
<i>♪ Yes, the classics
Are always fantastic! ♪</i>

04:50.441 --> 04:52.574
<i>♪ Oh, when newness
comes a-knockin' ♪</i>

04:52.617 --> 04:54.445
<i>♪ With that new type
Fast talkin' ♪</i>

04:54.489 --> 04:56.447
<i>♪ You young folks
Might think I'm lame ♪</i>

04:56.491 --> 04:58.493
<i>♪ But my answer
Is always the same ♪</i>

04:58.536 --> 05:00.843
<i>♪ What do I think of new?</i>

05:00.887 --> 05:02.976
<i>♪ Just ask my kazoo!</i>

05:03.019 --> 05:05.326
[playing kazoo to tune]

05:07.154 --> 05:09.852
So, this is the stuff you like
once you're older, huh?

05:09.896 --> 05:11.245
No.

05:11.288 --> 05:13.029
- [tooting]
- Come on, Tilly!

05:13.073 --> 05:14.770
You know you wanna!

05:14.814 --> 05:16.859
Tilly, don't you wanna go
up there with your Gramma?

05:16.903 --> 05:18.687
This song is perfect for Gramma,

05:18.730 --> 05:20.689
but again, I don't think
it works for me.

05:20.732 --> 05:23.823
Eh, her loss.
Time for another kazoo solo!

05:23.866 --> 05:25.868
Will Tilly ever find
where she belongs?

05:25.912 --> 05:27.652
[Kara Karaoke]
Excuse me, child.

05:27.696 --> 05:29.741
While you should not
choose your song in haste,

05:29.785 --> 05:31.352
time would not
choose it for you.

05:31.395 --> 05:33.876
So, in other words, please
hurry up and choose something

05:33.920 --> 05:36.270
- so others can have a turn.
- I'm sorry, family.

05:36.313 --> 05:37.967
I don't wanna be
a stick in the mud,

05:38.011 --> 05:40.317
but the lyrics to my song
need to be just right.

05:40.361 --> 05:43.364
Sister, sister, sister,
you're overthinking it.

05:43.407 --> 05:45.366
And overthinking
is the devil's other name.

05:45.409 --> 05:46.889
- Ain't that right, Remy?
- Yeah!

05:46.933 --> 05:48.848
Just don't think about
the lyrics.

05:48.891 --> 05:50.893
I don't know if I...
Oh, it's happening.

05:50.937 --> 05:54.288
<i>-♪ Uh, Cricket Green
-♪ Remy Remington</i>

05:54.331 --> 05:56.440
<i>♪ There's a lot of
Big questions
That make us feel small ♪</i>

05:56.464 --> 05:58.224
<i>♪ Why are we here?
What's the point of it all? ♪</i>

05:58.248 --> 06:00.424
<i>♪ Tell us to
Look in our books ♪</i>

06:00.468 --> 06:02.185
<i>♪ But to find the real answer
It's all about the hooks ♪</i>

06:02.209 --> 06:04.080
<i>♪ Don't think
About the lyrics ♪</i>

06:04.124 --> 06:05.952
<i>♪ Don't think about the beat</i>

06:05.995 --> 06:09.781
<i>♪ Just shake that booty
And get on your feet ♪</i>

06:09.825 --> 06:12.610
<i>♪ Just throw your hands up
And sway to this song ♪</i>

06:12.654 --> 06:14.917
<i>♪ 'Cause when you're dancing
You can't be wrong ♪</i>

06:14.961 --> 06:16.832
<i>♪ Whoa! Remy!</i>

06:16.876 --> 06:18.921
<i>♪ It wasn't curiosity
That killed the cat ♪</i>

06:18.965 --> 06:21.117
<i>♪ It was eighteen years
Of private education
Picture that ♪</i>

06:21.141 --> 06:23.012
<i>- ♪ Thinking is dumb!
- ♪ Oh!</i>

06:23.056 --> 06:25.014
<i>- ♪ Caring is dumb!
- ♪ Oh!</i>

06:25.058 --> 06:26.886
<i>- ♪ Parents are dumb?
- ♪ Oh!</i>

06:26.929 --> 06:28.583
<i>- ♪ Leave them behind?
- ♪ Oh!</i>

06:28.626 --> 06:30.367
<i>-♪ Hitch a ride on a train
-♪ Oh!</i>

06:30.411 --> 06:32.065
<i>- ♪ Become a carnie?
- ♪ Oh...</i>

06:32.108 --> 06:34.284
Uh, Cricket should we
really be saying all this?

06:34.328 --> 06:35.982
Don't think, Remy!

06:36.025 --> 06:37.592
<i>♪ Don't think
About the lyrics ♪</i>

06:37.635 --> 06:39.811
<i>♪ Don't think about this song</i>

06:39.855 --> 06:41.615
<i>♪ 'Cause when you're dancing
you can't be wrong ♪</i>

06:41.639 --> 06:43.163
<i>♪ Whoa!</i>

06:43.206 --> 06:45.078
[both panting]

06:45.121 --> 06:48.516
- Bad message! Bad message!
- Whoo-hoo! All right!

06:48.559 --> 06:50.953
- Wow, that was quite the...
- [horn toots]

06:50.997 --> 06:52.955
Would you make
a song decision, already?

06:52.999 --> 06:55.566
I put on this goofy hat
to sing some Ska!

06:55.610 --> 06:57.655
Does that little girl
have the programmer?

06:57.699 --> 06:59.962
I've been waiting to
make my Broadway debut!

07:00.006 --> 07:01.485
We wanna sing our duet!

07:01.529 --> 07:03.879
I wanna sing my
wickity-wickity-wack rap!

07:03.923 --> 07:06.708
Skrra! My dad's droppin' bars!

07:06.751 --> 07:08.101
[crowd complaining]

07:08.144 --> 07:09.929
- Hey!
- Back off!

07:09.972 --> 07:13.236
My-my-my-my-my-my-my-my-my!

07:13.280 --> 07:14.890
[gasps]
I have just hit my limit.

07:14.934 --> 07:16.936
- Hey, pick a song, already!
- Tilly!

07:16.979 --> 07:18.633
[slams, locks]

07:18.676 --> 07:21.853
Well, Tilly, the road of
indecision has brought us here.

07:21.897 --> 07:24.421
All alone,
hiding from an angry mob...

07:24.465 --> 07:26.467
on a toilet.

07:26.510 --> 07:29.035
Why are you
doing this to yourself?

07:29.078 --> 07:31.733
There are literally thousands
of songs to choose from.

07:31.776 --> 07:35.084
All you need to do is...
pick... one...

07:35.128 --> 07:37.304
Ugh! Or maybe
I should just resign myself

07:37.347 --> 07:39.915
to living in this bathroom
for the rest of my life.

07:39.959 --> 07:42.657
Tilly? I'm sure anything
you sing will be great.

07:42.700 --> 07:45.399
You don't understand!
I know it's silly, but...

07:45.442 --> 07:49.055
I just wanted to find a way
to truly express myself.

07:49.098 --> 07:52.362
You all got to sing songs
that were perfect for you,

07:52.406 --> 07:54.060
but no matter how hard I look,

07:54.103 --> 07:56.801
I just can't find a song
that's me.

07:56.845 --> 07:59.065
Maybe I'll never find
where I belong.

07:59.108 --> 08:00.849
- But...
- Dad, lemme try talking to her.

08:00.892 --> 08:02.546
[clears throat]
Tilly,

08:02.590 --> 08:04.113
the reason you
can't make a decision

08:04.157 --> 08:05.985
is 'cause your perfect song
doesn't exist.

08:06.028 --> 08:08.465
Dang it, Cricket, we're
trying to help your sister!

08:08.509 --> 08:09.901
- [door opens]
- Wait! That's it!

08:09.945 --> 08:11.860
I can't find my perfect song

08:11.903 --> 08:13.775
because it doesn't exist!

08:13.818 --> 08:15.081
Mwah! Thank you, brother!

08:15.124 --> 08:16.343
Wait, hold on, I...

08:16.386 --> 08:17.953
And that's how you do it.

08:17.997 --> 08:19.737
Mister,
here's the song programmer.

08:19.781 --> 08:21.261
So, you finally picked a song?

08:21.304 --> 08:22.740
What's goin' on?

08:23.959 --> 08:25.830
- [feedback]
- [deep breath]

08:25.874 --> 08:28.485
[a cappella] <i>
♪ I am Tilly Green</i>

08:28.529 --> 08:32.011
<i>♪ And I thought there was
No song for me ♪</i>

08:32.054 --> 08:34.839
<i>♪ Kept looking for something
pre-written ♪</i>

08:34.883 --> 08:37.581
<i>♪ A mold that I could fit in</i>

08:37.625 --> 08:38.930
What song is this?

08:38.974 --> 08:40.889
I think she's making up her own.

08:40.932 --> 08:43.892
<i>♪ But in all the tunes
That I perused ♪</i>

08:43.935 --> 08:46.895
<i>♪ Nothing felt Tilly true</i>

08:46.938 --> 08:49.985
<i>♪ I didn't think
I was such a puzzle ♪</i>

08:50.029 --> 08:53.293
<i>♪ All I wanted was
Something playful ♪</i>

08:53.336 --> 08:57.906
<i>♪ With just a hint
Of trouble! ♪</i>

08:57.949 --> 09:02.693
<i>♪ So, if you feel you're wrong
and don't belong ♪</i>

09:02.737 --> 09:07.176
<i>♪ Just do your own thing
And say so long ♪</i>

09:07.220 --> 09:12.051
<i>♪ Yeah, that's what I'm doing
When I sing this song! ♪</i>

09:12.094 --> 09:15.967
<i>♪ Yeah, it feels so good
To sing my song! ♪</i>

09:16.011 --> 09:18.840
<i>♪ If you're a fish
Out of water ♪</i>

09:18.883 --> 09:21.147
<i>♪ Maybe ya gotta dig
Your own lake ♪</i>

09:21.190 --> 09:23.540
<i>♪ If you can't find
The right color ♪</i>

09:23.584 --> 09:25.890
<i>♪ You just gotta mix
Your own paint ♪</i>

09:25.934 --> 09:28.458
<i>♪ Doesn't matter
If you're different ♪</i>

09:28.502 --> 09:30.895
<i>♪ So long as what you do
Is right for you ♪</i>

09:30.939 --> 09:33.115
<i>♪ Your uniqueness
Is a treasure ♪</i>

09:33.159 --> 09:37.119
<i>♪ Sharing differences
Brings us together, ooh ♪</i>

09:37.163 --> 09:41.297
<i>♪ If you feel you're wrong
And don't belong ♪</i>

09:41.341 --> 09:46.041
<i>♪ Just do your own thing
And say so long ♪</i>

09:46.085 --> 09:50.828
<i>♪ Yeah, that's what I'm doing
As I make up this song! ♪</i>

09:50.872 --> 09:53.309
<i>♪ Yeah, it feels so good</i>

09:53.353 --> 09:56.921
<i>♪ To sing along</i>

09:56.965 --> 09:59.663
[just Tilly] <i>
♪ To Tilly's song!</i>

09:59.707 --> 10:01.187
[cheers and applause]

10:01.230 --> 10:03.058
So, sweetie, how do you feel?

10:03.102 --> 10:04.451
Like I belong.

10:04.494 --> 10:06.148
[all]
Aww, Tilly!

10:06.192 --> 10:07.454
Well done, my child.

10:07.497 --> 10:09.151
By looking within yourself,

10:09.195 --> 10:11.675
you were able to find
your true song.

10:11.719 --> 10:13.199
Well, thank you very much!

10:13.242 --> 10:15.331
Hey, since Tilly won
at karaoke, or whatever,

10:15.375 --> 10:16.811
do we get a prize, or something?

10:16.854 --> 10:18.160
There never was a prize.

10:18.204 --> 10:20.162
Your satisfaction
with expressing your soul

10:20.206 --> 10:21.468
should be its own reward.

10:21.511 --> 10:23.209
Since when is satisfaction
a reward?

10:23.252 --> 10:25.602
At least give me
a bad t-shirt I'll never wear!

10:25.646 --> 10:27.865
I think it's time
we call it a night, brother.

10:27.909 --> 10:29.867
Will the next performer
come to the mic, please?

10:29.911 --> 10:31.782
[ska music playing]

10:31.826 --> 10:34.916
♪ <i>I got sweat in my eyes</i> ♪

10:34.959 --> 10:38.963
♪ <i>Lost a bet and
Got bit by a hundred flies ♪</i>

10:39.007 --> 10:41.749
♪ <i>I fell out a big old tree</i> ♪

10:41.792 --> 10:44.926
♪ <i>Hit every branch and
Scraped up both my knees ♪</i>

10:44.969 --> 10:48.538
♪ <i>I got chased by dogs
Licked by a frog ♪</i>

10:48.582 --> 10:50.149
♪ <i>Got a rash on my legs</i> ♪

10:50.192 --> 10:52.194
♪ <i>Dropped a dozen eggs</i> ♪

10:52.238 --> 10:53.804
♪ <i>I got splinters</i> ♪

10:53.848 --> 10:55.980
♪ <i>In seven of ten</i> ♪

10:56.024 --> 10:58.679
♪ <i>And tomorrow
I'll do it all again ♪</i>
